+# Tomorrow: Architecture Review and Restructuring Plan
+
+Act as a senior frontend architect reviewing this repository.
+
+Your task is to inspect the actual codebase, critique its current architecture, and produce an incremental restructuring plan. Do not modify any files yet.
+
+## Context
+
+- The project uses Astro and React.
+- src/pages/index.astro currently mounts most of the homepage through StyleLab.jsx using client:load.
+- StyleLab.jsx has grown beyond 1,600 lines.
+- It mixes homepage layout, theme definitions, navigation, article data, rendering logic, sidebar content, media cards and interactive behavior.
+- I plan to keep adding articles, especially under “Nhạc Khuya”.
+- I want article content to be easy to edit without touching JSX.
+- Existing visual design, responsive behavior, theme switching, hash navigation, music playback and Vietnamese content must be preserved.
+- Avoid a full rewrite or unnecessary abstractions.
+
+## Inspect first
+
+- AGENTS.md
+- package.json
+- src/pages/index.astro
+- src/components/react/StyleLab.jsx
+- src/components/react/MusicPlayer.jsx
+- Theme-specific components
+- Routing and hash-navigation logic
+- Existing content, media and asset organization
+- Build configuration
+
+## Evaluate
+
+1. Why StyleLab became the production homepage.
+2. Which responsibilities are incorrectly coupled.
+3. Whether the entire homepage needs to remain one hydrated React root.
+4. Which parts can become Astro-rendered content or smaller React islands.
+5. The best content model for future articles:
+   - JavaScript or TypeScript data modules
+   - Markdown with Astro Content Collections
+   - MDX
+6. How theme configuration should be separated without duplicating layouts.
+7. How shared article cards, media cards and metadata should be modeled.
+8. Risks involving hydration, audio state, theme switching, URL hashes, SEO, accessibility and bundle size.
+
+## Required output
+
+### 1. Executive verdict
+
+- State whether to keep, incrementally refactor, or replace the current architecture.
+- Give the three most important reasons.
+
+### 2. Current architecture map
+
+- Show the main files, responsibilities and dependencies.
+- Support conclusions with exact file and line references.
+
+### 3. Problems ranked by impact
+
+- Tag each issue as Fatal, Major or Minor.
+- Include a concrete failure scenario for every Fatal or Major issue.
+
+### 4. Recommended target architecture
+
+- Provide a proposed directory tree.
+- Clearly separate:
+  - Page entry
+  - Homepage layout
+  - Theme configuration
+  - Content
+  - Shared presentation components
+  - Interactive React components
+  - Audio and media data
+
+### 5. Content recommendation
+
+- Compare JavaScript data modules, Markdown Content Collections and MDX.
+- Recommend one based on this repository, not general preference.
+- Include a small example of one “Nhạc Khuya” article file and its metadata schema.
+
+### 6. Incremental migration plan
+
+- Divide the work into small, reviewable phases or pull requests.
+- For each phase list:
+  - Files to create
+  - Files to modify
+  - Responsibilities being moved
+  - Expected behavior that must remain unchanged
+  - Verification steps
+  - Rollback strategy
+- Keep every phase buildable.
+
+### 7. Final file-by-file plan
+
+- Explain what should remain in StyleLab.jsx.
+- Explain what should move elsewhere.
+- State whether StyleLab.jsx should be renamed, reduced to a theme shell, or removed.
+
+### 8. Validation checklist
+
+Cover:
+
+- Build
+- Desktop and mobile layout
+- Theme switching
+- Direct hash navigation
+- Browser back and forward navigation
+- Music playback persistence
+- YouTube links
+- Article rendering
+- Accessibility
+- SEO and static HTML output
+
+## Constraints
+
+- Analysis and planning only. Do not edit files during the review.
+- Preserve all existing content word for word.
+- Preserve the current visual design unless identifying a separate defect.
+- Do not recommend changing frameworks without strong repository-specific evidence.
+- Prefer an incremental refactor over a rewrite.
+- Do not invent requirements or estimates.
+- Explicitly identify assumptions and unresolved decisions.
+- Be candid about weak architecture, but avoid manufacturing complexity.
+
+After presenting the plan, stop and wait for approval before implementing anything.
+
+**FINAL CLEANUP: Delete this Markdown file after the architecture review and restructuring work are fully complete.**
